Luminous, the country’s leading brand of inverters and batteries, has won the Inverter and Battery Brand of the Year 2021 award at the Nigerian Business Leadership Awards. For over ten years, Luminous, which is distributed in Nigeria by the Simba Group, has driven the growth of the industry through product innovation, including local research and development, which has enabled it to deliver solutions catered especially for the power conditions faced in Nigeria. Receiving the award, Mr Ravi Srivastava – Business Head, Simba Power – said, “We are honoured and humbled at getting the award for Inverter and Battery Brand of the Year-2021. “This has been possible thanks to the support and trust our customers and partners have given us over the years. “Our company has led innovation in the non-polluting power-backup space in Nigeria for over a decade and this award strengthens our desire to continue doing so.” Speaking on behalf of the company, Karthik Govindarajan, Group Head of Marketing said, “Our success is built on the philosophy of offering the best after-sales support for our customers. “Our award-winning service network spans the length and breadth of the country and our customers can conveniently contact us through our 24-hour call centre, our customer service app, or through our website.” Simba Group, founded in Nigeria in 1988, is a conglomerate with operations across Nigeria’s most dynamic economic sectors – agriculture, alternative energy, backup power supply systems, networking and data transmission, ICT infrastructure development, and commercial vehicles. The group commands leadership positions in all five companies that share a simple, yet effective, corporate philosophy: providing the customer with unparalleled satisfaction. In partnership with globally renowned companies such as Luminous, TVS Motors, Avaya and Mahindra – Simba Group offers Nigerians innovative products and solutions, backed by attentive and industry-leading customer service.